en_1353745_0	COLOMBO (News 1st) – The Urban Development Authority states it has commenced a study in order to gather information on the families that were affected by the Easter Sunday terror attacks.
en_1353745_1	The Chairman of the authority, Ranjith Shantha Kahawala noted that the study was initiated based on the instructions of Minister of Housing, Construction and Cultural Affairs Sajith Premadasa.
en_1353745_2	The chairman added that they have already ascertained the statistics on injured and deceased persons at St. Sebastian Church blast site in Katuwapitiya.
en_1353745_3	He further noted that collecting statistics in other blast sites are already underway.
